review_data: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2019
name: Kat
title: What's not to love?
review: I discovered this product a few years ago at a Whole Foods. I love cream on the top full-fat yogurt, so as soon as I saw this had that, I was sold.I prefer the blueberry best from their fruit yogurts. The strawberry one is great tasting, but unlike the blueberry yogurt where the berries remain firm, like most strawberry yogurts, it tastes more like jam mixed in due to the limp strawberries and the extra sugars released.Still, having tried many yogurts in my life, this one is always in my top two brands. It's creamy consistency is the same as the other brands, so you really can't lose. Plus,it's organic and the taste is real, not fake.
